results.name: a(n) is the least positive number not already used that is coprime to the previous floor(n/2) terms.
comment: a(n) is coprime to the next n terms. - _David Wasserman_, Oct 24 2005
All values up to a(1000000) are either prime powers or semiprimes; this suggests the sequence is unlikely to be a permutation of the integers.
It appears that a(n) is even iff n = 3*2^k-1 for some k. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 01 2014
